.el .ds Aq '
.TH carbonado-encode 1  "carbonado-encode " 
.SH NAME
carbonado\-encode \- Encode a file or directory into a Carbonado archive
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcarbonado\-encode\fR [\fB\-f\fR|\fB\-\-format\fR] [\fB\-\-outboard\fR] [\fB\-\-encrypted\fR] [\fB\-\-master\fR] [\fB\-o\fR|\fB\-\-output\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fIINPUT\fR> 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Encode a file or directory into a Carbonado archive
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-f\fR, \fB\-\-format\fR \fI<LEVEL>\fR [default: 14]
Format level 0–15 (default 14 = public verifiable; odd values = encrypted)
.TP
\fB\-\-outboard\fR
Single\-file only: bare main + `.out`/`.par` sidecars (default single\-file is inboard)
.TP
\fB\-\-encrypted\fR
Directory only: encrypted catalog c15 and segment formats c13/c15 (auto\-creates BIP39 seed if needed)
.TP
\fB\-\-master\fR \fI<HEX>\fR
32\-byte master key as 64 hex chars (overrides stored BIP39 seed)
.TP
\fB\-o\fR, \fB\-\-output\fR \fI<DIR>\fR
Output directory [single\-file default: . ; directory default: {input}\-archive/]
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
<\fIINPUT\fR>
Input file or directory
